	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>678 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.16]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>If you can't find azure sleeves, which on Druzzil Ro run for about 1K, look for gatorscale sleeves.&nbsp;&nbsp;I think they're about half the price, and it's an Upper Guk item and therefore should be more prevalent.<br><br>I'm not 100% certain, but logic and my experience strongly suggest that your off hand will swing at the delay of the off-hand weapon, and will be subject to a dual wield skill check every swing.  It makes no sense to have your off hand's swing rate dictated by your primary - otherwise you could put a super-slow monster club off hand and speed it up.  <br><br>But, more importantly, your weapon combo information is all spelled out here.<br><br><a href="http://tinaddar.kung-foo.org/monk1hb.html" target=_new>http://tinaddar.kung-foo.org/monk1hb.html</a> <br><br>You should put your Wu's in primary and your CoT in off hand.  That's an easy one.<br><br>Oh and get to work on your 2HB.  I made the mistake of letting it languish, and now I'm wasting valuable time doing non-experience practicing to get my 2HB up.<br><br>Keyeluke<br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 45th Circle<br>Strange Brew<br>Druzzil Ro<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></td></tr>
