	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>678 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.92]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Page about a third of the way down - you'll find everything you need to know.&nbsp;&nbsp;Osano's got a great post on the subject, and you'll find many more in the older posts on this board.<br><br>In summary, there are arguments favoring many different ways of splitting the points.  My personal opinion?  I'd do half Str half Sta.  You'll get agreement and dissent on this.  But you know what?  It's not that critical - you'll do OK with any of half a dozen different point strategies.  So stop going insane, read the old posts, do your points whatever way sounds best to you, and don't sweat it any longer.<br><br>Keyeluke<br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 45th Circle<br>Strange Brew<br>Druzzil Ro</p>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></td></tr>
