	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99237254685414>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=3&mid=99237254685414>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99237254685414>Feign Death / Instill Doubt Training Macro for Fighting</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99237254685414#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Jun 12th 3:02 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=634><span id=Scholar>Altizar</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>104 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.20]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>As you all know Feign Death and Instill Doubt are the toughest skills to raise.&nbsp;&nbsp;You get sick and tired of hitting those buttons again and again, so I made the following macro to train these two skills WHILE YOU FIGHT and not miss any combat dmg.  I was able to raise my FD skill 30 points and ID 10 points in 1 day and still get 2 levels.  <br><br>To make things easy assign your Feign Death skill to ability slot 1 and your Instill Doubt skill to ability slot 2.<br><br>Create a Social Macro and call it whatever you want "Train" is good enough.  Put in the following commands 1 per line.<br><br>/doability 2  -- start your Instill Doubt motion<br>/doability 1  -- Preform your Feign Death<br>/sit off -- Stand up<br>/attack on -- resume attacking<br><br>As you can see there are no pauses in here so the FD, stand up, and attack are almost instantaneous<br><br>Keep in mind this should be done while you are attacking because you goal is not to actually preform a successful FD, but to train the skill.<br><br>Also the recover rate on both these skill seems to be the same, so they can be trained in sequence like this.<br><br>Here's another quick Macro I use to increase my Sense Heading.  Assign Sense Heading to Ability 3.<br><br>/doability 3<br>/pause 16<br>/doability 3<br>/pause 16<br>/doability 3<br><br>This will let you do 3 senses by only hitting 1 button.  I tried to do /pause 16 doability 3 like you would use in setting up a casters spell, but the skill doesn't seem to trigger, do a /bug and report it as a bug, cause then you could do 5 sense headings with only 1 key press ;)<br><br>Edit: After looking at my skills, I noticed one was lagging behind. (Yes, I'm a skill slut)  My sneak was way behind all the other, so I decided to see If I could work this in to the macro.<br><br>/doability 2  -- start your Instill Doubt motion<br>/doability 1  -- Perform your Feign Death<br>/sit off -- Stand up<br>/doabilty 3 -- Perform Sneak<br>/attack on -- resume attacking<br><br>The result was pretty good, got 10 skill increase on sneak after I started using it.  Also the recycle time on sneak fits in with ID/FD, however you usually need to hit the Sneak skill button again to stop sneaking, kinda a pain to have a runner, and the you crawl after him in sneak mode.  You can rearrange the order of these skills, though I'd say keep FD as the last one.<br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
