	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>678 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.40]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Easy.&nbsp;&nbsp;Bamboo bo stick.  8/20 weighs 1.0 lbs and should cost you less than 100pp.  Nice and fast, lets you get your 2HB up quickly.  Certainly not the weapon the adamantite is.<br><br>On the other hand, at your level I don't think you're facing too huge a penalty for carrying around the big stick.  Do an experiment - go to the bank, equip and unequip it, and see how much your AC changes.  It's a hell of a whupping stick for a lvl 11 and you're probably just fine eating the weight penalty for a few more levels at least.  You don't mention what your 1HB weapons are.  If you don't have any thing good, you might consider selling the Adamantite Bo, buying a Fighting Baton and Essence of Dol for maybe 700 pp, and spending the rest on some good AC gear - maybe some gem inlaid gauntlets, a foreman's tunic, or one of half a dozen other nice monk-friendly low to mid range items.<br><br>Keyeluke<br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 45th Circle<br>Strange Brew<br>Druzzil Ro</p>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></td></tr>
