	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>171 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.78]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Monks are awesome (ok, I'm biased, I admit it) -- stick with it.<br><br>Level 12 is a bit too early for Oasis.&nbsp;&nbsp;Could you survive in a good croc group? Yes. But you'd be better off elsewhere.  Just head north a bit to North Ro and get in a derv group, or solo Tarantulas and Scarabs.  Go to WC and fight Young Kodiaks and Wisps or group at the Orcs and Dervs.  If you feel like travelling, head for BlackBurrow and look for a Gnoll Elite group.  Return to Oasis at level 15 or so and you'll be much happier.<br><br>Put the fighting baton in your primary hand and use your fist offhand.  Much better damage output, and you'll still get good skill-ups in both 1HB and H2H.<br><br>Your stats are ... uh ... rather impressive for level 12 ... for a human monk anyway ... I guess you're probably Iksar, but it still sounds damn good to me.  No other comment there.<br><br>Dual wield is active if you are using any combination of fists and 1HB.  Not active for 2HB.<br><br>1HB, 2HB, and H2H should ALL be kept maxed if at all possible.  H2H for low levels, 1HB for mid-levels, 2HB for high levels prior to Epic, then back to H2H for epic.  This is general, barring any surprising/twink weaponry for your level, and ignoring certain specific situations.<br><br>Skill points -- SAVE for FD, ID.  'Nuff said.<br><br>Good Luck.<br><br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></td></tr>
