	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>678 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.52]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I see a lot of monks fighting with a Jade Mace primary and KD off-hand.&nbsp;&nbsp;Osano's right - there are some really insane drops in places like Veeshan's Peak, and some crazy no-drop stuff (look up Stronghorn's horn), but us mere mortals don't get to consider those until we (hopefully) get to our mid/high 50s.  Jade Mace seems to be the best primary 1HB for us monkeys (just got my paws on one) short of miracle weapons.  In off hand, another jade mace actually looks to be a hair better than the KD, though the difference is slight and the KD is a cheaper weapon to buy.  The jade mace is superior to the Wu's stick - costs twice as much, too ;).  In fact, without the proc, the Wu's stick is no better in terms of damage output than the basic fighting baton.  The proc is what makes the Wu's better, and is probably why people pay 7K instead of 500 for it.<br><br>My personal dream is to get a Stave of Shielding for off-hand.  Been to Chardok once - nasty little place (managed to get killed twice - casters DD for 520 multiple times), but a party of 40s and low 50s can camp the exit if they're careful, and the stave is supposedly a very rare but obtainable drop.  Plus, it's not no-drop, though I don't think I've ever seen one for sale.<br><br>Keyeluke<br>Monk of the Silent Fist - 45th Circle<br>Strange Brew<br>Druzzil Ro</p>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></td></tr>
