	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Jun 10th 3:49 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>171 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.54]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well, I'm not level 50 yet, but I've read up on this.&nbsp;&nbsp;Forget 1HB, for taunt the Celestial Fists are nuts.  On the other hand, there are LOTS of ways to manage aggro during a fight.  A lot of high level monks repeatedly drop and pop after each attack round (macro for this) to keep reducing aggro.  If you time this right, you lose next to nothing in your attack.  There are other strategies depending upon what kind of class combination may be in your group.<br><br>On the other hand, in the high-end game, you probably WILL want to use 2HB until you get your Celestial Fists, unless you get some kind of dragon drop gear for 1HB.</p>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></td></tr>
