	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;   Im using an adamantite bo stick, and it doesnt proc yet, but since it is an AE proc, should i get another 2hb weap once i hit lvl 36 when i believe it starts to proc.  I'm considering 2 other weapons- Stormwood battle staff, or Baton of Faith.  Baton of faith is better with stats of 30-40, and stormwood is something like 26-40, but Stormwood has the 96 dd, which would be nice.<br>     Also, whats better- my adamantite bo stick, which im hitting from 20-50 dmg with, or CoT and essence of dol at lvl 28 almost 29?<br><br>Thanks<br>28th human monk<br>Teraw-Marr<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>1 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99220177335758>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=3&mid=99220177335758>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99220177335758>RE: procs</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99220177335758#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Jun 10th 3:36 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>171 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.74]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Adamantite Bo procs starting at level 30.&nbsp;&nbsp;Personally, I LOVE this weapon, and think those who give it up once it starts to proc are making a mistake.  While the proc limits the number of situations in which it can be used, if you learn how to deal with the AOE effect, it is a VERY powerful 2HB.<br><br>Basically, use it for outdoor fights in non-chanter groups or to solo outdoors.  It *can* be used (in certain instances) in dungeons or even with a mez/assist group, but you better *really* know what you're doing in those situations.<br><br>If you are fighting a medium-to-small mob you will almost always take one hit of the proc, for a max of 47 damage (often less depending on your level and MR).  Then again, unless the MOB resists, it's taking 225.  This is nearly always a good trade-off.  Plus, if you're fighting large or giant MOBs, you shouldn't take ANY waves of the proc.  Just make sure you're near the limit of melee range (this takes a bit of practice, but is not hard to do).<br><br>The easiest way to practice with this weapon is to find a MOB that is green, but has at least 500HP, so that it will take all 3 waves before running (unless the weapon procs late in the fight).  I used Crag Spiders in EK.  Now, switch to a long-range view.  When the weapon procs, back up until you are just at the edge of the proc range -- you'll only take one wave, you'll still have the MOB engaged, and the MOB will take all three waves.  Once you get used to how much you need to back up, you can remain in first person view -- it's just easier to see the proc edge from long view.<br><br>If the MOB starts to run, pull the weapon to your curser and run it down with fists.  No sense having it proc when the mob is running away -- you'll just run through your own proc and do needless damage to yourself.  I have my weapon slot hot-keyed to my main fighting bank for this purpose.  Makes it real easy to switch to fists.<br><br>Based on my experience to date with the weapon, I would estimate that it procs once for each 750 HP of regular damage you do with it.  This is an average over a lot of fights.  Sometimes it won't proc at all, sometimes it will chain proc 3 or more times.  Now, assuming, on average, one partial resist from a level 35 MOB, net of the one wave of 47 max damage that you will take, this effectively increases the weapon's damage output by about 20% -- making this a great 2HB if used properly, and an absolute KILLER when fighting Giants.<br><br>Edit to add:  I just started soloing Wooly Mammoths in EW with this thing -- they're large enough that you don't get hit by the proc.  They also ID kite reasonably well (skill 200 though).  Apparantly, I *underestimated* the proc potential of the weapon.  I had fought mostly Drakkel Dire wolves previously and had to keep backing up.  The weapon seems to proc MUCH more if you can stay in one place.  Most of the time, I can take down a Wooly solo with only 2 bubbles of health gone.  Of course, if the thing doesn't proc, and I don't get an ID chain kite off, I have to FD out of the battle most of the time, as these guys have a LOT of HP and hit hard.<br><br>Also, DON'T use this if grouped with someone using a pet.  The proc WILL hit the pet and you'll have Jobaber beating on you along with the MOB -- not a lot of fun.  Figure out if the proc or the pet is preferred and go with one or the other.  You may still be able to use the weapon *and* a pet against a Giant -- it will depend on what range the pet fights the MOB at -- I haven't had a chance to test this yet.<br><br>Edit to add:  Supposedly, according to a post I just read, the situation where the AOE hits pets was fixed in a previous patch.  So, that may not be an issue, but I haven't tested this yet.<br><br>As for the rest of your questions -- don't worry about it -- keep the 'suicide stick' : )</p>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></td></tr>
